{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567203","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567203"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:57:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:57:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18946"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18946","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18946"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.21,0.05,0.57,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11680"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80513"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11680","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11680"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18946"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65802"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11280"},{"type":"tags","id":"11281"},{"type":"tags","id":"11286"},{"type":"tags","id":"11302"},{"type":"tags","id":"11397"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27482"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27485"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80513","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80513"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA second-year medical student is working on a written assignment about the pathophysiology of heart failure. The student uses an artificial intelligence chatbot to generate several paragraphs of text, which they then incorporate directly into their assignment.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate academic assessment of this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Permissible if used for less than 20% of the assignment","Acceptable if the generated text is fact checked by student and correct","Acceptable if the student edits the generated text","Constitutes academic misconduct","Permissible if used for less than 10% of the assignment"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis situation represents \u003Cstrong\u003Eacademic misconduct\u003C/strong\u003E. Using artificial intelligence to generate text that is presented as one\u0027s own work without acknowledgment is a form of plagiarism. Students must declare any use of artificial intelligence tools in their academic work, just as they would cite any other source.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcceptable if the generated text is factually correct\u003C/strong\u003E - The accuracy of the content does not affect the requirement to acknowledge sources\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPermissible if used for less than 10% or 20% of the assignment\u003C/strong\u003E - There is no acceptable threshold for unacknowledged use of AI-generated content\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcceptable if the student edits the generated text\u003C/strong\u003E - Editing AI-generated content does not remove the requirement to acknowledge its use\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStudents should consult their institution\u0027s policies regarding the use of artificial intelligence tools in academic work. When permitted, such tools should be used responsibly with appropriate attribution, and their outputs should be critically evaluated for accuracy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Using artificial intelligence to generate written assignments without acknowledgment constitutes academic misconduct.","Students must declare any use of artificial intelligence tools in their academic work.","Artificial intelligence outputs may contain factual errors and should not be used without critical evaluation and verification."],"references":["Khalifa M, Albadawy M. Using artificial intelligence in academic writing and research: An essential productivity tool. Computer Methods and Programs in Biomedicine Update. 2024;5:100145. Available at: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2666990024000120","Tertiary Education Quality and Standards Agency (TEQSA). Artificial intelligence and academic integrity: emerging concerns. Melbourne (AU): TEQSA; 2022."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65802"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18946"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65802","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65802"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-21T11:17:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-21T11:19:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11680"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80513"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null